Write code to change color of text red and green if any error occurs in Angular18







Perfect üëç let‚Äôs solve this step by step.

We‚Äôll make Angular show text red if there is an error and green if success.





---



‚úÖ Step 1: Create a Component (example: status-message.component.ts)



import { Component } from '@angular/core';



@Component({

  selector: 'app-status-message',

  templateUrl: './status-message.component.html',

  styleUrls: ['./status-message.component.css']

})

export class StatusMessageComponent {

  message: string = '';

  isError: boolean = false;



  showSuccess() {

    this.message = 'Property saved successfully!';

    this.isError = false;

  }



  showError() {

    this.message = 'Something went wrong while saving property!';

    this.isError = true;

  }

}





---



‚úÖ Step 2: Template (HTML) ‚Üí status-message.component.html



<div [ngClass]="{ 'error-text': isError, 'success-text': !isError }">

  {{ message }}

</div>



<button (click)="showSuccess()">Show Success</button>

<button (click)="showError()">Show Error</button>





---



‚úÖ Step 3: CSS ‚Üí status-message.component.css



.error-text {

  color: red;

  font-weight: bold;

}



.success-text {

  color: green;

  font-weight: bold;

}





---



üîé How it Works:



When you click Show Success, message appears in green.



When you click Show Error, message appears in red.



ngClass is used to toggle CSS class based on isError flag.







---



üí° Project Example (Buy & Sell Properties App)



When a property is added successfully ‚Üí show green "Property added successfully".



When API call fails ‚Üí show red "Failed to add property".







---



